# Riverside Prototype - Cursor AI Rules

## CRITICAL: Always Use Riverstyle Design System

This is a Riverside prototype project. You MUST use the `@riversidefm/riverstyle` design system for ALL UI work.

**Live Storybook:** https://storybook.rs-prod.riverside.fm/

### ⚠️ ICONS: Always Check the Icon Set FIRST!

**Most icons exist in the Riverstyle icon set.** Before creating ANY custom SVG icon, you MUST:

1. **Check the icon folder:** `ls node_modules/@riversidefm/riverstyle/icons/{category}/`
2. **Search all categories** - the icon might be in an unexpected folder
3. **Find the file name** (e.g., `home-05.svg.js`)
4. **Convert to component:** `Icons.{Category}.{PascalCaseName}` (e.g., `Icons.General.Home05`)

Example conversions:

- `home-05.svg.js` → `Icons.General.Home05`
- `folder.svg.js` → `Icons.Files.Folder`
- `calendar.svg.js` → `Icons.Time.Calendar`
- `podcast.svg.js` → `Icons.MediaDevices.Podcast`
- `user-plus-01.svg.js` → `Icons.Users.UserPlus01`
- `video-recorder.svg.js` → `Icons.MediaDevices.VideoRecorder`

**Only if an icon truly doesn't exist** after checking all categories, you may create a custom SVG following the design style.

**🎨 IMPORTANT: Download SVGs from Figma, don't create them manually!**
If an icon doesn't exist in Riverstyle, use the Figma MCP tool to download the SVG:

```
mcp_Figma_Desktop_get_design_context with dirForAssetWrites parameter
```

This exports the exact SVG from Figma to `/public/icons/`. Never try to recreate SVGs by hand.

**See the Icons section below for full documentation.**

### Required CSS Import

The design system CSS is imported in `src/main.tsx`:

```tsx
import "@riversidefm/riverstyle/styles.css";
```

### Required Component Imports

Always import components from the design system:

```tsx
import {
  Button,
  LinkButton,
  IconButton,
  Input,
  InputField,
  Checkbox,
  Switcher,
  Typography,
  Avatar,
  Toast,
  Tabs,
  Popover,
  Tooltip,
  TooltipIcon,
  Spinner,
  DefaultSelect,
  Icons,
} from "@riversidefm/riverstyle";
```

### Color Tokens (ALWAYS USE THESE)

NEVER use hardcoded colors. Always use these CSS variables:

#### Primary Colors (Purple)

- `var(--color-primary-c100)` - #f2eeff (lightest)
- `var(--color-primary-c200)` - #e7dfff
- `var(--color-primary-c300)` - #d5c7ff
- `var(--color-primary-c400)` - #c3afff
- `var(--color-primary-c500)` - #b196ff
- `var(--color-primary-c600)` - #9671ff
- `var(--color-primary-c700)` - #875eff
- `var(--color-primary-c800)` - #7848ff (main primary)
- `var(--color-primary-c900)` - #5e3ac3 (darkest)

#### Secondary Colors (Grays)

- `var(--color-secondary-c100)` - #fafafa (white-ish)
- `var(--color-secondary-c150)` - #dbdbdb
- `var(--color-secondary-c200)` - #bbbbbb
- `var(--color-secondary-c300)` - #888888
- `var(--color-secondary-c400)` - #555555
- `var(--color-secondary-c500)` - #444444
- `var(--color-secondary-c600)` - #383838
- `var(--color-secondary-c700)` - #2b2b2b
- `var(--color-secondary-c800)` - #222222
- `var(--color-secondary-c900)` - #1d1d1d
- `var(--color-secondary-c1000)` - #151515
- `var(--color-secondary-c1100)` - #0d0d0d (darkest)

#### Base Colors

- `var(--color-white)` - #ffffff
- `var(--color-black)` - #0a0a0a

#### State Colors

- `var(--color-success-c500)` to `var(--color-success-c800)` - Greens
- `var(--color-warning-c500)` to `var(--color-warning-c800)` - Yellows
- `var(--color-error-c400)` to `var(--color-error-c800)` - Reds
- `var(--color-upgrade-c500)` to `var(--color-upgrade-c800)` - Lime greens

#### Accent Colors

- `var(--color-purple)` - #b43dff
- `var(--color-light-purple)` - #b377ff
- `var(--color-pink)` - #e961ff
- `var(--color-dark-blue)` - #5353fc
- `var(--color-light-blue)` - #50c9ff
- `var(--color-green)` - #67ffb1
- `var(--color-neon)` - #c2ff44
- `var(--color-yellow)` - #ffec45
- `var(--color-orange)` - #ff8a00

#### Transparent Colors

- `var(--color-transparent-c10)` to `var(--color-transparent-c75)` - Black transparencies
- `var(--color-transparent-p10)` to `var(--color-transparent-p50)` - Purple transparencies
- `var(--color-transparent-w10)` / `var(--color-transparent-w30)` - White transparencies
- `var(--color-modal-overlay)` - rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5)

### Typography Tokens (ALWAYS USE THESE)

#### Font Family

- `var(--font-family-main)` - Inter, sans-serif

#### Headings

```css
font: var(--font-heading-xlarge); /* 800 36px/44px */
font: var(--font-heading-large); /* 700 28px/36px */
font: var(--font-heading-medium); /* 800 24px/20px */
font: var(--font-heading-small); /* 800 20px/24px */
font: var(--font-heading-xsmall); /* 800 16px/24px */
font: var(--font-heading-xxsmall); /* 700 14px/20px */
letter-spacing: var(--font-heading-xlarge-spacing); /* etc. */
```

#### Body Text

```css
font: var(--font-body-xlarge); /* 500 20px/28px */
font: var(--font-body-large); /* 500 16px/24px */
font: var(--font-body-medium); /* 400 14px/24px */
font: var(--font-body-small); /* 500 12px/18px */
letter-spacing: var(--font-body-medium-spacing); /* etc. */
```

#### Labels & Links

```css
font: var(--font-label-medium); /* 500 14px/20px */
font: var(--font-label-small); /* 600 12px/20px */
font: var(--font-link-medium); /* 600 14px/20px */
font: var(--font-link-small); /* 700 12px/20px */
font: var(--font-helper); /* 500 11px/20px */
font: var(--font-tip); /* 600 11px/16px */
font: var(--font-tiny-label); /* 500 10px/16px */
```

### Component Usage Examples

#### Button

Button variants include the height in the name: `{type}-{height}`

- Types: `primary`, `secondary`, `tertiary`, `ghost`, `danger`, `upgrade`, `blurry`
- Heights: `48`, `44`, `40`, `36`, `32` (pixels)

```tsx
// Standard buttons (48px height is default/most common)
<Button variant="primary-48" onClick={() => {}}>Primary</Button>
<Button variant="secondary-48" onClick={() => {}}>Secondary</Button>
<Button variant="ghost-48" onClick={() => {}}>Ghost</Button>
<Button variant="tertiary-48" onClick={() => {}}>Tertiary</Button>

// Smaller buttons
<Button variant="primary-36" onClick={() => {}}>Small Primary</Button>
<Button variant="secondary-32" onClick={() => {}}>Tiny Secondary</Button>

// Special variants
<Button variant="danger-48" onClick={() => {}}>Delete</Button>
<Button variant="upgrade-48" onClick={() => {}}>Upgrade</Button>

// Loading state
<Button variant="primary-48" loading onClick={() => {}}>Loading...</Button>
```

#### Input

```tsx
<Input placeholder="Enter text..." />
<Input error="This field is required" />

// For labeled inputs, use InputField with props objects:
<InputField
  inputProps={{ placeholder: "you@example.com" }}
  labelProps={{ label: "Email" }}
  errorProps={{ message: "" }}
/>
```

#### Typography Component

All available variants (camelCase):

- Headings: `headingXLarge`, `headingLarge`, `headingMedium`, `headingSmall`, `headingXSmall`, `headingXXSmall`
- Body: `bodyXlarge`, `bodyLarge`, `bodyMedium`, `bodySmall`
- Labels: `labelMedium`, `labelSmall`
- Links: `linkMedium`, `linkSmall`
- Other: `tinyLabel`, `helper`, `tip`, `avatar`

Color tokens (dot notation):

- Primary: `primary.c100` to `primary.c900`
- Secondary: `secondary.c100` to `secondary.c1100`
- Success: `success.c500` to `success.c800`
- Warning: `warning.c500` to `warning.c800`
- Error: `error.c400` to `error.c800`
- Upgrade: `upgrade.c500` to `upgrade.c800`
- System: `white`, `black`

```tsx
<Typography variant="headingLarge">Title</Typography>
<Typography variant="bodyMedium">Body text</Typography>
<Typography variant="labelSmall">Label</Typography>
<Typography variant="bodyMedium" color="primary.c800">Primary color</Typography>
<Typography variant="bodyMedium" color="secondary.c300">Muted text</Typography>
<Typography variant="bodyMedium" color="error.c700">Error text</Typography>
<Typography variant="bodyMedium" color="success.c700">Success text</Typography>
```

#### Icons

> ⚠️ **CRITICAL: NEVER create custom SVG icons!** All icons exist in the Riverstyle icon set.
> Icons are from [Untitled UI Icons](https://www.untitledui.com/icons) plus custom Riverside icons.

**How to find the correct icon name:**

1. **Browse the icon files** in `node_modules/@riversidefm/riverstyle/icons/`
2. **Convert file name to component name** using this pattern:
   - File: `home-05.svg.js` → Component: `Icons.General.Home05`
   - File: `user-plus-01.svg.js` → Component: `Icons.Users.UserPlus01`
   - File: `video-recorder.svg.js` → Component: `Icons.MediaDevices.VideoRecorder`

**Naming Convention:**

- Kebab-case file names become PascalCase component names
- Numbers stay at the end: `settings-01` → `Settings01`
- Hyphens are removed: `arrow-right` → `ArrowRight`

```tsx
import { Icons } from '@riversidefm/riverstyle'

// General icons (from node_modules/@riversidefm/riverstyle/icons/general/)
<Icons.General.Home05 style={{ width: 24, height: 24 }} />        // home-05.svg.js
<Icons.General.Settings01 style={{ width: 24, height: 24 }} />    // settings-01.svg.js
<Icons.General.Settings02 style={{ width: 24, height: 24 }} />    // settings-02.svg.js
<Icons.General.Plus style={{ width: 24, height: 24 }} />          // plus.svg.js
<Icons.General.Check style={{ width: 24, height: 24 }} />         // check.svg.js
<Icons.General.XClose style={{ width: 24, height: 24 }} />        // x-close.svg.js
<Icons.General.SearchMd style={{ width: 24, height: 24 }} />      // search-md.svg.js
<Icons.General.HelpCircle style={{ width: 24, height: 24 }} />    // help-circle.svg.js

// Files icons (from node_modules/@riversidefm/riverstyle/icons/files/)
<Icons.Files.Folder style={{ width: 24, height: 24 }} />          // folder.svg.js
<Icons.Files.File01 style={{ width: 24, height: 24 }} />          // file-01.svg.js

// Time icons (from node_modules/@riversidefm/riverstyle/icons/time/)
<Icons.Time.Calendar style={{ width: 24, height: 24 }} />         // calendar.svg.js
<Icons.Time.Clock style={{ width: 24, height: 24 }} />            // clock.svg.js

// Users icons (from node_modules/@riversidefm/riverstyle/icons/users/)
<Icons.Users.UserPlus01 style={{ width: 24, height: 24 }} />      // user-plus-01.svg.js
<Icons.Users.User01 style={{ width: 24, height: 24 }} />          // user-01.svg.js

// MediaDevices icons (from node_modules/@riversidefm/riverstyle/icons/media-devices/)
<Icons.MediaDevices.Podcast style={{ width: 24, height: 24 }} />       // podcast.svg.js
<Icons.MediaDevices.VideoRecorder style={{ width: 24, height: 24 }} /> // video-recorder.svg.js
<Icons.MediaDevices.Microphone01 style={{ width: 24, height: 24 }} />  // microphone-01.svg.js

// Arrows icons (from node_modules/@riversidefm/riverstyle/icons/arrows/)
<Icons.Arrows.ArrowRight style={{ width: 24, height: 24 }} />     // arrow-right.svg.js
<Icons.Arrows.ChevronDown style={{ width: 24, height: 24 }} />    // chevron-down.svg.js

// AlertsFeedback icons (from node_modules/@riversidefm/riverstyle/icons/alerts-feedback/)
<Icons.AlertsFeedback.Announcement01 style={{ width: 24, height: 24 }} />  // announcement-01.svg.js
<Icons.AlertsFeedback.Bell01 style={{ width: 24, height: 24 }} />          // bell-01.svg.js
```

**Icon Categories (folder names in node_modules/@riversidefm/riverstyle/icons/):**

| Category         | Folder              | Example Icons                                                          |
| ---------------- | ------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `General`        | `/general/`         | Home05, Settings01, Plus, Check, SearchMd, HelpCircle, Edit01, Trash01 |
| `Arrows`         | `/arrows/`          | ArrowRight, ArrowLeft, ChevronDown, ChevronUp                          |
| `AlertsFeedback` | `/alerts-feedback/` | Announcement01, Bell01, AlertCircle, InfoCircle                        |
| `Files`          | `/files/`           | Folder, File01, FileText, Clipboard                                    |
| `Time`           | `/time/`            | Calendar, Clock, AlarmClock                                            |
| `Users`          | `/users/`           | User01, UserPlus01, Users01                                            |
| `MediaDevices`   | `/media-devices/`   | Podcast, VideoRecorder, Microphone01, Play, Pause                      |
| `Communications` | `/communications/`  | Mail01, Phone, MessageSquare                                           |
| `Editor`         | `/editor/`          | Bold, Italic, Underline                                                |
| `Magic`          | `/magic/`           | MagicClips, MagicCaptions, SmartLayouts                                |
| `Riverside`      | `/riverside/`       | Webinar (custom Riverside icons)                                       |

**To find an icon:**

1. Check the folder: `ls node_modules/@riversidefm/riverstyle/icons/{category}/`
2. Find the file name (e.g., `home-05.svg.js`)
3. Convert to component: `Icons.{Category}.{PascalCaseName}`

**Browse icons visually:** https://www.untitledui.com/icons

#### If Icon Doesn't Exist - Download from Figma

**⚠️ NEVER create custom SVG icons by hand!** If an icon doesn't exist in Riverstyle:

1. **Get the node ID** from the Figma design (e.g., from the URL or layer)
2. **Use the Figma MCP tool** to download the SVG:

```
mcp_Figma_Desktop_get_design_context({
  nodeId: "1234:5678",
  dirForAssetWrites: "/path/to/project/public/icons"
})
```

3. **Reference the downloaded SVG** in your component:

```tsx
// Icon downloaded from Figma to /public/icons/
const customIcon = '/icons/abc123.svg'

// Use in component
<img src={customIcon} alt="" style={{ width: 20, height: 20 }} />
```

This ensures pixel-perfect accuracy with the original Figma design.

#### IconButton

IconButton variants: `{type}-{size}`

- Types: `ghost`, `secondary`, `round-primary`, `round-secondary`, `blurry`
- Sizes: `44`, `40`, `36`, `32`, `24`
- ⚠️ NOTE: IconButton does NOT have `primary` or `danger` variants (use regular Button for those)

```tsx
<IconButton variant="ghost-44" icon={Icons.General.Settings01} aria-label="Settings" onClick={() => {}} />
<IconButton variant="secondary-44" icon={Icons.General.Plus} aria-label="Add" onClick={() => {}} />
<IconButton variant="round-primary-44" icon={Icons.General.Check} aria-label="Confirm" onClick={() => {}} />
<IconButton variant="round-secondary-44" icon={Icons.General.XClose} aria-label="Close" onClick={() => {}} />
<IconButton variant="blurry-44" icon={Icons.General.SearchMd} aria-label="Search" onClick={() => {}} />
```

#### Checkbox

```tsx
<Checkbox
  name="fieldName"
  checked={checked}
  onChange={(e) => setChecked(e.target.checked)}
/>
```

#### Switcher

```tsx
<Switcher
  checked={on}
  onChange={(checked) => setOn(checked)}
  aria-label="Toggle feature"
/>
```

#### Avatar

```tsx
<Avatar variant="circle-24">AB</Avatar>
<Avatar variant="circle-32">CD</Avatar>
<Avatar variant="circle-40">EF</Avatar>
```

#### Tabs

```tsx
<Tabs value={activeTab} onChange={setActiveTab}>
  <Tabs.Tab value="tab1">First Tab</Tabs.Tab>
  <Tabs.Tab value="tab2">Second Tab</Tabs.Tab>
</Tabs>
```

#### DefaultSelect

```tsx
const options = [
  { id: '1', label: 'Option 1' },
