// Add container to your app once
<Toast.Container />;

// Show toasts
Toast.tasks.success("Success message");
Toast.tasks.error("Error message");
Toast.tasks.info("Info message");
```

#### Popover

```tsx
const ref = useRef<HTMLButtonElement>(null)

<Button variant="secondary-48" onClick={() => setOpen(true)} reference={ref}>
  Open Popover
</Button>
<Popover
  opened={open}
  onClose={() => setOpen(false)}
  reference={ref}
  placement="bottom-start"
>
  <div>Popover content</div>
</Popover>
```

#### TooltipIcon

```tsx
<TooltipIcon content="Helpful information here" />
```

### Card/Surface Pattern

```tsx
<div
  style={{
    background: "var(--color-secondary-c900)",
    borderRadius: "12px",
    padding: "24px",
    border: "1px solid var(--color-secondary-c700)",
  }}
>
  <Typography variant="headingSmall">Card Title</Typography>
  <Typography
    variant="bodyMedium"
    style={{ color: "var(--color-secondary-c300)" }}
  >
    Card description
  </Typography>
</div>
```

### File Structure

- `/src/pages/` - Page components (add new pages here)
- `/src/components/my-components/` - Custom components (ONLY when Riverstyle doesn't have it)
- `/src/pages/PrototypePage.tsx` - Riverstyle component showcase
- `/src/pages/MyComponentsPage.tsx` - Custom components showcase

### Reference

- **Local:** Visit `/riverstyle` in the running app for embedded Storybook
- **Local:** Visit `/my-components` to see custom components
- **Live:** https://storybook.rs-prod.riverside.fm/

---

## Creating Custom Elements (When Design System Doesn't Cover It)

The design system doesn't cover everything. When you need something custom, follow these guidelines:

### Before Creating Custom - MANDATORY CHECKS:

1. **Search Riverstyle Storybook** - https://storybook.rs-prod.riverside.fm/
   - Check ALL categories: Base, Combined, Form, Selects
   - Search by name and by function
2. **Check if it can be composed** from existing Riverstyle components
   - Can you combine Button + Typography + Icons?
   - Can you use existing form components?
3. **Check similar patterns** in the existing codebase

   - Has someone already built this?

4. **Confirm 3+ times** that the component truly doesn't exist

### If Component TRULY Doesn't Exist - Create in `/src/components/my-components/`

```tsx
// src/components/my-components/MyCustomCard.tsx

import { Typography, Icons } from "@riversidefm/riverstyle";

interface MyCustomCardProps {
  title: string;
  children: React.ReactNode;
}

export function MyCustomCard({ title, children }: MyCustomCardProps) {
  return (
    <div
      style={{
        // ✅ MUST use Riverstyle color tokens
        background: "var(--color-secondary-c900)",
        border: "1px solid var(--color-secondary-c700)",
        borderRadius: "12px",
        padding: "24px",
      }}
    >
      {/* ✅ MUST use Typography component */}
      <Typography variant="headingSmall">{title}</Typography>

      <div
        style={{
          // ✅ MUST use color and font tokens
          color: "var(--color-secondary-c300)",
          font: "var(--font-body-medium)",
          marginTop: "12px",
        }}
      >
        {children}
      </div>
    </div>
  );
}
```

### Custom Component Rules (MANDATORY):

1. **Colors** - ONLY use `var(--color-*)` tokens, NEVER hex values
2. **Typography** - Use `<Typography>` component or `var(--font-*)` tokens
3. **Icons** - Import from `@riversidefm/riverstyle`, not custom SVGs
4. **Theme** - Follow dark theme (secondary-c900+ for backgrounds)
5. **Accents** - Use primary-c800 (#7848ff) for brand color
6. **Export** - Add export to `/src/components/my-components/index.ts`
7. **Showcase** - Add demo to `/my-components` page

### Custom Component Rules (MANDATORY):

- ✅ **Colors** - ONLY use `var(--color-*)` tokens, NEVER hardcode hex values
- ✅ **Typography** - Use `<Typography>` component or `var(--font-*)` tokens
- ✅ **Icons** - Use Riverstyle icons first; only create custom if truly not available
- ✅ **Theme** - Follow dark theme (secondary-c900+ for backgrounds)
- ✅ **Accents** - Use primary-c800 (#7848ff) for brand color

---

### Priority Order (ALWAYS Follow This)

1. **First:** Check if Riverstyle has the component, icon, color, or style
2. **Second:** Check if you can compose it from existing Riverstyle elements
3. **Third:** Only then create custom, using Riverstyle tokens

### DO NOT (General)

- ❌ Use hardcoded hex colors - use `var(--color-*)` tokens
- ❌ Use arbitrary font sizes - use `var(--font-*)` tokens
- ❌ Skip checking Riverstyle before creating custom elements
- ❌ Use font families other than Inter
- ❌ Guess icon names - look up the actual file in the icons folder
- ❌ Create custom icons without first checking ALL icon categories
- ❌ Try to use icons that doesn't exist that would cause errors.

### DO (General)

- ✅ **Always check Riverstyle first** for components, icons, colors, typography
- ✅ Use CSS variables for all colors and typography
- ✅ Reference Storybook before creating anything custom
- ✅ Maintain the dark theme aesthetic (use secondary-c900+ for backgrounds)
- ✅ Use primary-c800 (#7848ff) as the main brand accent
- ✅ Put custom components in `/src/components/my-components/` folder
- ✅ **Look up icon file names** in `node_modules/@riversidefm/riverstyle/icons/{category}/`
- ✅ **Convert icon file names** to PascalCase: `home-05.svg.js` → `Icons.General.Home05`
- ✅ Create custom elements when design system doesn't cover it (using design tokens)
